<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870921-0028 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Step-Saver Data Systems Inc.</HL><DD> 09/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CODA </IN><TEXT>   Step-Saver Data Systems Inc., Bala Cynwyd, Pa., said it expects to report a fiscal fourth-quarter net loss because of sluggish sales and increased expenses.    For the period ended June 30, the provider of computer business systems for the medical and legal professions estimated it will post a net loss of $426,000, compared with year-earlier net income of $190,723, which included $144,470 from the settlement of litigation.    Step-Saver said it expects to report a net loss of $184,000 for the fiscal year. The company had year-earlier earnings of $435,611, or 10 cents a share. </TEXT></DOC>